lumber /ˈlʌmbə/

(lumbering,lumbered,lumbers) 

1. N-UNCOUNT Lumber consists of trees and large pieces of wood that have been roughly cut up. 木材 [美国英语] 

例： It was made of soft lumber, spruce by the look of it. 它是软木做的，看样子是云杉。 

2. V-I If someone or something lumbers from one place to another, they move there very slowly and clumsily. 缓慢笨拙地移动 

例： He lumbered back to his chair. 他蹒跚地坐回到椅子上。 

3. V-I to burden with something unpleasant, tedious, etc 使烦恼; 烦扰 [英国英语] [非正式]

